    <glossary>
        <definition id="import-auto-id1169737931448"><term>wavelength in a medium</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169738220318"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>λ</m:mi><m:mrow> <m:mtext>n</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>λ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{λ rSub { size 8{n} } =λ/n} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, where <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>λ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{λ} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the wavelength in vacuum, and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{n} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the index of refraction of the medium</meaning></definition>
    </glossary>
